{
  "doc_id": "14016",
  "text": "Design optimization affected by process introduced variations has been a focus of recent research efforts [CITATION_1] - [CITATION_2] . How to formulate the design optimization depends on the models of variations. Indeed, it has also been pointed by [CITATION_3] that \"solutions to optimization problems can exhibit remarkable sensitivity to perturbations in the parameter\". Process variations are generally modeled as random variables. A nature way is to formulate design optimization affected by parameter uncertainty as a stochastic optimization problem. In this section we will use gate sizing, a typical circuit design problem, as an example to explain how to employing the notion of uncertainty budgeting to translate a in general NP-hard stochastic problem [CITATION_4] into a tractable robust optimization problem.",
